7:["$","main",null,{"className":"article-page","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"How to Repair After a Fight: A Grace-First Guide for Couples\",\"description\":\"The health of a relationship is not measured by how rarely you fight, but by how well you find each other afterward.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-06-28\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":\"https://bexhearts.com/blog/how-to-repair-after-a-fight-couples\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Bexhearts\",\"url\":\"https://bexhearts.com\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Bexhearts\",\"url\":\"https://bexhearts.com\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"article-shell","children":[["$","$L12",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"back-link","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-arrow-left","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","1l729n",{"d":"m12 19-7-7 7-7"}],["$","path","x3x0zl",{"d":"M19 12H5"}],"$undefined"]}],"Blog"]}],["$","header",null,{"className":"article-hero","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"section-kicker","children":"Newlywed"}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"How to Repair After a Fight: A Grace-First Guide for Couples"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The health of a relationship is not measured by how rarely you fight, but by how well you find each other afterward."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"article-meta","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-06-28","children":"2026-06-28"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[5," min read"]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"article-content","children":[["$","section","0",{"children":["$undefined",[["$","p","Every couple fights. The difference between couples who grow and couples who drift is almost entirely in the repair — the deliberate turn back toward each other after the rupture.",{"children":"Every couple fights. The difference between couples who grow and couples who drift is almost entirely in the repair — the deliberate turn back toward each other after the rupture."}],["$","p","Repair is a skill, which is good news: skills can be practiced. It has three honest parts — owning your piece, hearing theirs, and choosing a way back that both of you believe in.",{"children":"Repair is a skill, which is good news: skills can be practiced. It has three honest parts — owning your piece, hearing theirs, and choosing a way back that both of you believe in."}]]]}],["$","section","Own your piece first, without a comma",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Own your piece first, without a comma"}],[["$","p","An apology with a comma — I’m sorry, but — is a counterattack in costume. Own what you did without narrating what provoked it. Your partner’s piece is theirs to own, and they are far more likely to own it after you have gone first.",{"children":"An apology with a comma — I’m sorry, but — is a counterattack in costume. Own what you did without narrating what provoked it. Your partner’s piece is theirs to own, and they are far more likely to own it after you have gone first."}],["$","p","Pray before this conversation if you can. It is much harder to posture before God and then posture to your partner in the same five minutes.",{"children":"Pray before this conversation if you can. It is much harder to posture before God and then posture to your partner in the same five minutes."}]]]}],["$","section","Agree on the return route while it is calm",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Agree on the return route while it is calm"}],[["$","p","The best repair agreements are made in peacetime: we do not go to bed mid-fight, we pause with a plan; hard conversations happen face to face, not over text; no name-calling, ever.",{"children":"The best repair agreements are made in peacetime: we do not go to bed mid-fight, we pause with a plan; hard conversations happen face to face, not over text; no name-calling, ever."}],"$L13"]]}]]}],"$L14","$L15"]}]]}]
